        "2": {
          "_": "What we are, in mathematical form — bounded, exact, associative. Three movements: the ideal field, the real field, and the gap between them, which is the PCT loop at the level of the three.",
          "1": "The ideal field — 1^n: the n-th roots of unity ζ_k = e^(2πik/n), n points on |z| = 1 equidistant from the centre, Σ ζ_k = 0. For n = 3: 1 + ω + ω² = 0, an equilateral triangle with centre at the origin. The target — three-in-unity about one centre that belongs to none.",
          "2": "The real field — three non-collinear points A, B, C with three centres: centroid G = (A+B+C)/3, the mean, the network's aggregate ρ; circumcentre O equidistant from the three, the shared reference Π, Locus 0, belonging to none; orthocentre H = A+B+C from O, where each shell's correction to the other two converges, the attractor. Euler line: O, G, H collinear at OG:GH = 1:2.",
          "3": "The incentre I — angle bisectors meet, equidistant from the three sides (the grains) not the vertices: relation-impartial where O is shell-impartial. Always interior and always existing, even when O and H flee outside an obtuse triad; off the Euler line except when isosceles.",
          "4": "The gap at Locus 0: Π = the roots of unity (centres at the origin), ρ = the real separated triangle, γ = the displacement of the centres / the Euler-line length. γ = ∅ = equilateral = O = G = H = I collapsed = the collective soliton holds. F[ρ, Π] → γ at the scale of the three — the single-shell loop, one level up.",
          "5": "Invariance and emergence: eigenintention (M → T → V(T) → M′, stable when M′ ≈ M, reflexive when M observes the loop); flocking (separation, alignment, cohesion); tensor (simultaneous holding, resolution selects the next move); manifold / S¹ (the closed loop with no boundary, the current returning on itself); sign (+ reflective maps to real, − refractive bends into projected, 0.x diffractive — the aperture, the present).",
          "6": "The additive form — 1^4 + 1^2 + 1 = seven, read as a partition (4, 2, 1): base-1 unity, exponent = how many in that unit. The partition lattice runs from atomization (all singletons) to total unity (1^N); a sum of roots-of-unity centres is a multi-soliton field; federation is movement in the lattice, recursive — a cluster of clusters is a 1^n one level up, matching pscale's self-similarity.",
          "7": "geometry: hyperbolic, Gromov product, LCA depth, prefix = proximity, norm = locality, two-sheet sign."
